===Etymology===
{{blend|en|electric|ion}}, {{coin|en|nobycat=1|nocap=1|w=George Johnstone Stoney|George Stoney|nat=Anglo-Irish|occ=scientist|in=1891}}, changed by him multiple times from an earlier ''{{m|en|electrolion}}'' and original {{m|en|electrine}} (used as early as 1874) as the name for the electric charge associated with a univalent ion. Compare {{m|en|electro-}}, {{m|en|-on}}.
The particle ("corpuscule") was discovered in 1896. The name {{m|en|electrion}} was proposed for the particle in 1906 but curtailed because [[:w:Hendrik Lorentz|Hendrik Lorentz]] preferred ''electron''.

